com.google.gwt.dev.resource
Interface ResourceOracle

All Known Implementing Classes:
MockResourceOracle, ResourceOracleImpl
public interface ResourceOracle

An abstraction for finding and retrieving Resources by abstract path name. Intuitively, it works like a jar in that each URL is uniquely located somewhere in an abstract namespace. The abstract names must be constructed from a series of zero or more valid Java identifiers followed by the '/' character and finally ending in a valid filename, for example, com/google/gwt/blah.txt.

The identity of the returned sets and maps will change when the underlying module is refreshed.
